The suspect, Olusanya A 35-year-old woman, Monsurat Olusanya, has been arrested by detectives of Ogun State police command for inflicting severe injuries on the body of a four-year-old girl, Fathia Ogundimu, who is reported to be her niece. Her arrest followed a complaint from a Community Development Association (CDA) member of Tiluwalase town in Owode Ijako (name withheld), who came to Sango Division Headquarters with the little girl on Friday, October 18, and reported that the girl is on the verge of being sent to an early grave if appropriate steps were not taken to save the little girl from her ‘wicked’ aunty. According to the Ogun police spokesman, Abimbola Oyeyemi, “the suspect who accused the girl of mistakenly pouring a pot of soup away put a knife on fire and used the hot knife to inflict injuries all over the girl’s body. Not satisfied, she gave the baby human bite on her stomach and lips. “On the strength of the report, the DPO Sango police station, CSP Godwin Idehai, detailed his detectives to the scene where the aunty was promptly arrested. On interrogation, she admitted been responsible for the injuries on the body of the victim but pleaded with the police to be lenient with her claiming that devil pushed her to do it. The victim has been taken to hospital for medical treatment. “The suspect, who is a mother of three, is currently being detained at Sango division while the biological parents of the victim have been contacted for them to come and take custody of their daughter”. Meanwhile, the commissioner of police, CP Bashir Makama, has directed that the suspect be charged to court as investigation is concluded. The police boss also appealed to parents to know the type of people they give their children to if at all there is need to do so as many of the so-called guardians these days are in the habit of maltreating children who are not their own. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .